{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":708,"text":"As someone who has spent his entire career trying to be invisible"}]},{"cues":[{"time":5000,"text":"standing in front of an audience is a cross between"},{"time":8000,"text":"an out-of-body experience and a deer caught in the headlights,"},{"time":11000,"text":"so please forgive me for violating one of the TED commandments"},{"time":16000,"text":"by relying on words on paper,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and I only hope I'm not struck by lightning bolts before I'm done."},{"time":22000,"text":"I'd like to begin by talking about some of the ideas that motivated me"},{"time":27000,"text":"to become a documentary photographer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"I was a student in the '60s, a time of social upheaval and questioning,"},{"time":35000,"text":"and on a personal level, an awakening sense of idealism."},{"time":39000,"text":"The war in Vietnam was raging;"},{"time":42000,"text":"the Civil Rights Movement was under way;"},{"time":44000,"text":"and pictures had a powerful influence on me."},{"time":47000,"text":"Our political and military leaders were telling us one thing,"},{"time":50000,"text":"and photographers were telling us another."},{"time":53000,"text":"I believed the photographers, and so did millions of other Americans."},{"time":58000,"text":"Their images fueled resistance to the war and to racism."},{"time":62000,"text":"They not only recorded history; they helped change the course of history."},{"time":67000,"text":"Their pictures became part of our collective consciousness"},{"time":70000,"text":"and, as consciousness evolved into a shared sense of conscience,"},{"time":74000,"text":"change became not only possible, but inevitable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78000,"text":"I saw that the free flow of information represented by journalism,"},{"time":82000,"text":"specifically visual journalism, can bring into focus"},{"time":86000,"text":"both the benefits and the cost of political policies."},{"time":90000,"text":"It can give credit to sound decision-making, adding momentum to success."},{"time":95000,"text":"In the face of poor political judgment or political inaction,"},{"time":100000,"text":"it becomes a kind of intervention, assessing the damage"},{"time":104000,"text":"and asking us to reassess our behavior."},{"time":107000,"text":"It puts a human face on issues"},{"time":109000,"text":"which from afar can appear abstract"},{"time":112000,"text":"or ideological or monumental in their global impact."},{"time":115000,"text":"What happens at ground level, far from the halls of power,"},{"time":120000,"text":"happens to ordinary citizens one by one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123000,"text":"And I understood that documentary photography"},{"time":126000,"text":"has the ability to interpret events from their point of view."},{"time":130000,"text":"It gives a voice to those who otherwise would not have a voice."},{"time":134000,"text":"And as a reaction, it stimulates public opinion"},{"time":138000,"text":"and gives impetus to public debate,"},{"time":140000,"text":"thereby preventing the interested parties"},{"time":142000,"text":"from totally controlling the agenda, much as they would like to."},{"time":146000,"text":"Coming of age in those days made real"},{"time":149000,"text":"the concept that the free flow of information is absolutely vital"},{"time":152000,"text":"for a free and dynamic society to function properly."},{"time":156000,"text":"The press is certainly a business, and in order to survive"},{"time":160000,"text":"it must be a successful business,"},{"time":163000,"text":"but the right balance must be found"},{"time":165000,"text":"between marketing considerations and journalistic responsibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169000,"text":"Society's problems can't be solved until they're identified."},{"time":174000,"text":"On a higher plane, the press is a service industry,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and the service it provides is awareness."},{"time":181000,"text":"Every story does not have to sell something."},{"time":184000,"text":"There's also a time to give."},{"time":188000,"text":"That was a tradition I wanted to follow."},{"time":191000,"text":"Seeing the war created such incredibly high stakes for everyone involved"},{"time":195000,"text":"and that visual journalism could actually become a factor in conflict resolution --"},{"time":200000,"text":"I wanted to be a photographer in order to be a war photographer."},{"time":204000,"text":"But I was driven by an inherent sense"},{"time":207000,"text":"that a picture that revealed the true face of war"},{"time":210000,"text":"would almost by definition be an anti-war photograph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"I'd like to take you on a visual journey through some of the events"},{"time":218000,"text":"and issues I've been involved in over the past 25 years."},{"time":223000,"text":"In 1981, I went to Northern Ireland."},{"time":226000,"text":"10 IRA prisoners were in the process of starving themselves to death"},{"time":230000,"text":"in protest against conditions in jail."},{"time":233000,"text":"The reaction on the streets was violent confrontation."},{"time":236000,"text":"I saw that the front lines of contemporary wars"},{"time":240000,"text":"are not on isolated battlefields, but right where people live."},{"time":245000,"text":"During the early '80s, I spent a lot of time in Central America,"},{"time":249000,"text":"which was engulfed by civil wars"},{"time":251000,"text":"that straddled the ideological divide of the Cold War."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254000,"text":"In Guatemala, the central government --"},{"time":257000,"text":"controlled by a oligarchy of European decent --"},{"time":260000,"text":"was waging a scorched Earth campaign against an indigenous rebellion,"},{"time":264000,"text":"and I saw an image that reflected the history of Latin America:"},{"time":267000,"text":"conquest through a combination of the Bible and the sword."},{"time":271000,"text":"An anti-Sandinista guerrilla was mortally wounded"},{"time":275000,"text":"as Commander Zero attacked a town in Southern Nicaragua."},{"time":281000,"text":"A destroyed tank belonging to Somoza's national guard"},{"time":284000,"text":"was left as a monument in a park in Managua,"},{"time":288000,"text":"and was transformed by the energy and spirit of a child."},{"time":292000,"text":"At the same time, a civil war was taking place in El Salvador,"},{"time":296000,"text":"and again, the civilian population was caught up in the conflict."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301000,"text":"I've been covering the Palestinian-Israeli conflict since 1981."},{"time":306000,"text":"This is a moment from the beginning of the second intifada, in 2000,"},{"time":310000,"text":"when it was still stones and Molotovs against an army."},{"time":316000,"text":"In 2001, the uprising escalated into an armed conflict,"},{"time":319000,"text":"and one of the major incidents was"},{"time":321000,"text":"the destruction of the Palestinian refugee camp"},{"time":324000,"text":"in the West Bank town of Jenin."},{"time":328000,"text":"Without the political will to find common ground,"},{"time":332000,"text":"the continual friction of tactic and counter-tactic"},{"time":335000,"text":"only creates suspicion and hatred and vengeance,"},{"time":338000,"text":"and perpetuates the cycle of violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343000,"text":"In the '90s, after the breakup of the Soviet Union,"},{"time":346000,"text":"Yugoslavia fractured along ethnic fault lines, and civil war broke out"},{"time":351000,"text":"between Bosnia, Croatia and Serbia."},{"time":353000,"text":"This is a scene of house-to-house fighting in Mostar,"},{"time":357000,"text":"neighbor against neighbor."},{"time":359000,"text":"A bedroom, the place where people share intimacy,"},{"time":362000,"text":"where life itself is conceived, became a battlefield."},{"time":367000,"text":"A mosque in northern Bosnia was destroyed by Serbian artillery"},{"time":373000,"text":"and was used as a makeshift morgue."},{"time":382000,"text":"Dead Serbian soldiers were collected after a battle"},{"time":385000,"text":"and used as barter for the return of prisoners"},{"time":388000,"text":"or Bosnian soldiers killed in action."},{"time":392000,"text":"This was once a park."},{"time":394000,"text":"The Bosnian soldier who guided me"},{"time":396000,"text":"told me that all of his friends were there now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400000,"text":"At the same time in South Africa,"},{"time":402000,"text":"after Nelson Mandela had been released from prison,"},{"time":405000,"text":"the black population commenced the final phase"},{"time":408000,"text":"of liberation from apartheid."},{"time":411000,"text":"One of the things I had to learn as a journalist"},{"time":414000,"text":"was what to do with my anger."},{"time":416000,"text":"I had to use it, channel its energy, turn it into something"},{"time":421000,"text":"that would clarify my vision, instead of clouding it."},{"time":425000,"text":"In Transkei, I witnessed a rite of passage into manhood, of the Xhosa tribe."},{"time":430000,"text":"Teenage boys lived in isolation, their bodies covered with white clay."},{"time":435000,"text":"After several weeks, they washed off the white"},{"time":437000,"text":"and took on the full responsibilities of men."},{"time":440000,"text":"It was a very old ritual that seemed symbolic"},{"time":443615,"text":"of the political struggle that was changing the face of South Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450000,"text":"Children in Soweto playing on a trampoline."},{"time":457000,"text":"Elsewhere in Africa there was famine."},{"time":460000,"text":"In Somalia, the central government collapsed and clan warfare broke out."},{"time":465000,"text":"Farmers were driven off their land,"},{"time":467000,"text":"and crops and livestock were destroyed or stolen."},{"time":471000,"text":"Starvation was being used as a weapon of mass destruction --"},{"time":475000,"text":"primitive but extremely effective."},{"time":477000,"text":"Hundreds of thousands of people were exterminated,"},{"time":480000,"text":"slowly and painfully."},{"time":484000,"text":"The international community responded with massive humanitarian relief,"},{"time":488000,"text":"and hundreds of thousands of more lives were saved."},{"time":492000,"text":"American troops were sent to protect the relief shipments,"},{"time":495000,"text":"but they were eventually drawn into the conflict,"},{"time":498000,"text":"and after the tragic battle in Mogadishu, they were withdrawn."},{"time":502000,"text":"In southern Sudan, another civil war saw similar use of starvation"},{"time":506000,"text":"as a means of genocide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509000,"text":"Again, international NGOs, united under the umbrella of the U.N.,"},{"time":513000,"text":"staged a massive relief operation and thousands of lives were saved."},{"time":519000,"text":"I'm a witness, and I want my testimony to be honest and uncensored."},{"time":526000,"text":"I also want it to be powerful and eloquent,"},{"time":529000,"text":"and to do as much justice as possible"},{"time":531000,"text":"to the experience of the people I'm photographing."},{"time":534000,"text":"This man was in an NGO feeding center,"},{"time":537000,"text":"being helped as much as he could be helped."},{"time":539000,"text":"He literally had nothing. He was a virtual skeleton,"},{"time":544000,"text":"yet he could still summon the courage and the will to move."},{"time":548000,"text":"He had not given up, and if he didn't give up,"},{"time":551000,"text":"how could anyone in the outside world ever dream of losing hope?"},{"time":557000,"text":"In 1994, after three months of covering the South African election,"},{"time":562000,"text":"I saw the inauguration of Nelson Mandela,"},{"time":565000,"text":"and it was the most uplifting thing I've ever seen."},{"time":568000,"text":"It exemplified the best that humanity has to offer."},{"time":572000,"text":"The next day I left for Rwanda,"},{"time":575000,"text":"and it was like taking the express elevator to hell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"This man had just been liberated from a Hutu death camp."},{"time":582000,"text":"He allowed me to photograph him for quite a long time,"},{"time":586000,"text":"and he even turned his face toward the light,"},{"time":589000,"text":"as if he wanted me to see him better."},{"time":592000,"text":"I think he knew what the scars on his face would say to the rest of the world."},{"time":597000,"text":"This time, maybe confused or discouraged"},{"time":600000,"text":"by the military disaster in Somalia,"},{"time":603000,"text":"the international community remained silent,"},{"time":606000,"text":"and somewhere around 800,000 people were slaughtered"},{"time":609000,"text":"by their own countrymen -- sometimes their own neighbors --"},{"time":612000,"text":"using farm implements as weapons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616000,"text":"Perhaps because a lesson had been learned"},{"time":618662,"text":"by the weak response to the war in Bosnia"},{"time":621000,"text":"and the failure in Rwanda,"},{"time":623000,"text":"when Serbia attacked Kosovo,"},{"time":625000,"text":"international action was taken much more decisively."},{"time":628692,"text":"NATO forces went in, and the Serbian army withdrew."},{"time":633000,"text":"Ethnic Albanians had been murdered,"},{"time":635723,"text":"their farms destroyed and a huge number of people forcibly deported."},{"time":641000,"text":"They were received in refugee camps"},{"time":644000,"text":"set up by NGOs in Albania and Macedonia."},{"time":648538,"text":"The imprint of a man who had been burned inside his own home."},{"time":652585,"text":"The image reminded me of a cave painting,"},{"time":655554,"text":"and echoed how primitive we still are in so many ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661477,"text":"Between 1995 and '96, I covered the first two wars"},{"time":665523,"text":"in Chechnya from inside Grozny."},{"time":668000,"text":"This is a Chechen rebel on the front line against the Russian army."},{"time":674000,"text":"The Russians bombarded Grozny constantly for weeks,"},{"time":677646,"text":"killing mainly the civilians who were still trapped inside."},{"time":682169,"text":"I found a boy from the local orphanage"},{"time":684477,"text":"wandering around the front line."},{"time":688308,"text":"My work has evolved from being concerned mainly with war"},{"time":692000,"text":"to a focus on critical social issues as well."},{"time":696277,"text":"After the fall of Ceausescu, I went to Romania"},{"time":699000,"text":"and discovered a kind of gulag of children,"},{"time":703000,"text":"where thousands of orphans were being kept in medieval conditions."},{"time":707000,"text":"Ceausescu had imposed a quota"},{"time":709000,"text":"on the number of children to be produced by each family,"},{"time":712000,"text":"thereby making women's bodies an instrument of state economic policy."},{"time":717000,"text":"Children who couldn't be supported by their families"},{"time":720000,"text":"were raised in government orphanages."},{"time":723000,"text":"Children with birth defects were labeled incurables,"},{"time":726000,"text":"and confined for life to inhuman conditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730000,"text":"As reports began to surface, again international aid went in."},{"time":736000,"text":"Going deeper into the legacy of the Eastern European regimes,"},{"time":740000,"text":"I worked for several months on a story about the effects of industrial pollution,"},{"time":744000,"text":"where there had been no regard for the environment"},{"time":747000,"text":"or the health of either workers or the general population."},{"time":751000,"text":"An aluminum factory in Czechoslovakia"},{"time":754000,"text":"was filled with carcinogenic smoke and dust,"},{"time":757000,"text":"and four out of five workers came down with cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762400,"text":"After the fall of Suharto in Indonesia,"},{"time":764662,"text":"I began to explore conditions of poverty"},{"time":767431,"text":"in a country that was on its way towards modernization."},{"time":770662,"text":"I spent a good deal of time with a man"},{"time":774000,"text":"who lived with his family on a railway embankment"},{"time":776000,"text":"and had lost an arm and a leg in a train accident."},{"time":780000,"text":"When the story was published, unsolicited donations poured in."},{"time":785000,"text":"A trust fund was established,"},{"time":787000,"text":"and the family now lives in a house in the countryside"},{"time":790000,"text":"and all their basic necessities are taken care of."},{"time":793000,"text":"It was a story that wasn't trying to sell anything."},{"time":796000,"text":"Journalism had provided a channel"},{"time":799000,"text":"for people's natural sense of generosity, and the readers responded."},{"time":805000,"text":"I met a band of homeless children who'd come to Jakarta from the countryside,"},{"time":808000,"text":"and ended up living in a train station."},{"time":811000,"text":"By the age of 12 or 14, they'd become beggars and drug addicts."},{"time":816000,"text":"The rural poor had become the urban poor,"},{"time":818000,"text":"and in the process, they'd become invisible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824000,"text":"These heroin addicts in detox in Pakistan"},{"time":826600,"text":"reminded me of figures in a play by Beckett:"},{"time":829492,"text":"isolated, waiting in the dark, but drawn to the light."},{"time":837000,"text":"Agent Orange was a defoliant used during the Vietnam War"},{"time":840185,"text":"to deny cover to the Vietcong and the North Vietnamese army."},{"time":844123,"text":"The active ingredient was dioxin, an extremely toxic chemical"},{"time":849000,"text":"that was sprayed in vast quantities,"},{"time":851000,"text":"and whose effects passed through the genes to the next generation."},{"time":857000,"text":"In 2000, I began documenting global health issues,"},{"time":859662,"text":"concentrating first on AIDS in Africa."},{"time":862831,"text":"I tried to tell the story through the work of caregivers."},{"time":866000,"text":"I thought it was important to emphasize that people were being helped,"},{"time":870000,"text":"whether by international NGOs or by local grassroots organizations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874446,"text":"So many children have been orphaned by the epidemic"},{"time":877000,"text":"that grandmothers have taken the place of parents,"},{"time":880000,"text":"and a lot of children had been born with HIV."},{"time":884000,"text":"A hospital in Zambia."},{"time":889000,"text":"I began documenting the close connection"},{"time":892000,"text":"between HIV/AIDS and tuberculosis."},{"time":895000,"text":"This is an MSF hospital in Cambodia."},{"time":902600,"text":"My pictures can play a supporting role to the work of NGOs"},{"time":905338,"text":"by shedding light on the critical social problems they're trying to deal with."},{"time":910000,"text":"I went to Congo with MSF,"},{"time":913000,"text":"and contributed to a book and an exhibition"},{"time":915000,"text":"that focused attention on a forgotten war"},{"time":918000,"text":"in which millions of people have died,"},{"time":920000,"text":"and exposure to disease without treatment is used as a weapon."},{"time":925000,"text":"A malnourished child being measured"},{"time":927000,"text":"as part of the supplemental feeding program."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931000,"text":"In the fall of 2004 I went to Darfur."},{"time":935000,"text":"This time I was on assignment for a magazine,"},{"time":937000,"text":"but again worked closely with MSF."},{"time":939000,"text":"The international community still hasn't found a way"},{"time":942000,"text":"to create the pressure necessary to stop this genocide."},{"time":947062,"text":"An MSF hospital in a camp for displaced people."},{"time":952354,"text":"I've been working on a long project on crime and punishment in America."},{"time":957169,"text":"This is a scene from New Orleans."},{"time":962000,"text":"A prisoner on a chain gang in Alabama"},{"time":964338,"text":"was punished by being handcuffed to a post in the midday sun."},{"time":971000,"text":"This experience raised a lot of questions,"},{"time":973000,"text":"among them questions about race and equality"},{"time":976000,"text":"and for whom in our country opportunities and options are available."},{"time":981000,"text":"In the yard of a chain gang in Alabama."}]},{"cues":[{"time":986277,"text":"I didn't see either of the planes hit,"},{"time":988431,"text":"and when I glanced out my window, I saw the first tower burning,"},{"time":992000,"text":"and I thought it might have been an accident."},{"time":995000,"text":"A few minutes later when I looked again"},{"time":997000,"text":"and saw the second tower burning, I knew we were at war."},{"time":1002000,"text":"In the midst of the wreckage at Ground Zero, I had a realization."},{"time":1005215,"text":"I'd been photographing in the Islamic world since 1981 --"},{"time":1010000,"text":"not only in the Middle East, but also in Africa, Asia and Europe."},{"time":1014646,"text":"At the time I was photographing in these different places,"},{"time":1017615,"text":"I thought I was covering separate stories,"},{"time":1019646,"text":"but on 9/11 history crystallized, and I understood"},{"time":1023000,"text":"I'd actually been covering a single story for more than 20 years,"},{"time":1027400,"text":"and the attack on New York was its latest manifestation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1032000,"text":"The central commercial district of Kabul, Afghanistan"},{"time":1035000,"text":"at the end of the civil war,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"shortly before the city fell to the Taliban."},{"time":1042385,"text":"Land mine victims being helped"},{"time":1045000,"text":"at the Red Cross rehab center being run by Alberto Cairo."},{"time":1050000,"text":"A boy who lost a leg to a leftover mine."},{"time":1052615,"text":"I'd witnessed immense suffering in the Islamic world"},{"time":1056000,"text":"from political oppression, civil war, foreign invasions, poverty, famine."},{"time":1061000,"text":"I understood that in its suffering,"},{"time":1063000,"text":"the Islamic world had been crying out. Why weren't we listening?"},{"time":1070631,"text":"A Taliban fighter shot during a battle"},{"time":1073000,"text":"as the Northern Alliance entered the city of Kunduz."},{"time":1082738,"text":"When war with Iraq was imminent,"},{"time":1085000,"text":"I realized the American troops would be very well covered,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"so I decided to cover the invasion from inside Baghdad."},{"time":1097000,"text":"A marketplace was hit by a mortar shell"},{"time":1099000,"text":"that killed several members of a single family."},{"time":1104000,"text":"A day after American forces entered Baghdad,"},{"time":1107000,"text":"a company of Marines began rounding up bank robbers"},{"time":1109000,"text":"and were cheered on by the crowds --"},{"time":1112000,"text":"a hopeful moment that was short lived."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115200,"text":"For the first time in years,"},{"time":1117369,"text":"Shi'ites were allowed to make the pilgrimage"},{"time":1119692,"text":"to Karbala to observe Ashura,"},{"time":1122000,"text":"and I was amazed by the sheer number of people"},{"time":1124585,"text":"and how fervently they practiced their religion."},{"time":1130000,"text":"A group of men march through the streets cutting themselves with knives."},{"time":1133000,"text":"It was obvious that the Shi'ites were a force to be reckoned with,"},{"time":1137000,"text":"and we would do well to understand them and learn how to deal with them."},{"time":1144000,"text":"Last year I spent several months documenting our wounded troops,"},{"time":1147692,"text":"from the battlefield in Iraq all the way home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1151246,"text":"This is a helicopter medic giving CPR"},{"time":1153708,"text":"to a soldier who had been shot in the head."},{"time":1158062,"text":"Military medicine has become so efficient"},{"time":1160585,"text":"that the percentage of troops who survive after being wounded"},{"time":1164400,"text":"is much higher in this war than in any other war in our history."},{"time":1169646,"text":"The signature weapon of the war is the IED,"},{"time":1173000,"text":"and the signature wound is severe leg damage."},{"time":1177369,"text":"After enduring extreme pain and trauma,"},{"time":1180569,"text":"the wounded face a grueling physical"},{"time":1183000,"text":"and psychological struggle in rehab."},{"time":1187369,"text":"The spirit they displayed was absolutely remarkable."},{"time":1191538,"text":"I tried to imagine myself in their place,"},{"time":1194000,"text":"and I was totally humbled by their courage and determination"},{"time":1198000,"text":"in the face of such catastrophic loss."},{"time":1201462,"text":"Good people had been put in a very bad situation for questionable results."},{"time":1209492,"text":"One day in rehab someone, started talking about surfing"},{"time":1213000,"text":"and all these guys who'd never surfed before said, \"Hey, let's go.\""},{"time":1217338,"text":"And they went surfing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1222585,"text":"Photographers go to the extreme edges of human experience"},{"time":1226000,"text":"to show people what's going on."},{"time":1228000,"text":"Sometimes they put their lives on the line,"},{"time":1231000,"text":"because they believe your opinions and your influence matter."},{"time":1235000,"text":"They aim their pictures at your best instincts,"},{"time":1239000,"text":"generosity, a sense of right and wrong,"},{"time":1242000,"text":"the ability and the willingness to identify with others,"},{"time":1246000,"text":"the refusal to accept the unacceptable."},{"time":1251000,"text":"My TED wish:"},{"time":1253000,"text":"there's a vital story that needs to be told,"},{"time":1256000,"text":"and I wish for TED to help me gain access to it"},{"time":1260000,"text":"and then to help me come up with innovative and exciting ways"},{"time":1264000,"text":"to use news photography in the digital era."},{"time":1267000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1270000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}